result.execSummary:
The defendant Amanda L Daniels was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Amanda L Daniels in court with attorney Robert A Kennedy.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 10:09 AM. Kennedy has ROAW, no inaccurracies but would like address information in regards to why probation failed. Court will allow statement after the state's recommendation. State recommending, Count 1 - one year in FC jail and Count 3 - 9 months FC jail, concurrent. All parties stipulate to 167 days of credit. State makes final statement. Kennedy makes statement and asks for a 7 month sentence. Daniels makes statement, remorseful, asks for time served. Court sentences to the following: Count 1 - 300 days in FC jail; Count 3 - 9 months in FC jail, concurrent, with good time and huber, elibible for community service under 973.03(3). Credit for 167 days. Pay fines & fees within 60 days after release of incarrceration. Right to appeal.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on October 2, 2017 at 09:30 am.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Amanda L Daniels in court with attorney Lindsay L Erickson.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:00 AM. Called 16CM15 and 16CM16. State - resolved on both matters, on 16CM15 - amend to county ordinance of possession of THC with a forfeiture of $300.00 plus costs totalling $582.50, on 16CM16 - plead to counts #1 and #3 as alleged, #2 - DRI, 120 days jail on each count as probation was rejected - concurrent to each other, costs only on count #3 and $100 fine plus costs on count #1. Daniels and Erickson agree. Court - 16CM15 - amend only count to county ordinance of possession of THC - pleads NC, finds G, fine of $300.00 plus costs totalling $582.50 - 60 DTP/CO after argument for longer time to pay/payment plan. Erickson again makes argument for payment plan or longer time. Court still gives 60 DTP/CO but will stay it to 60 days from release from inpatient if court receives proof that the defendant is in inpatient treatment. Court - 16CM16 - dismisses and reads in count #2. Daniels pleads NC to counts #1 and #3 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Erickson disagrees with what the State has said in regards to the sentence. Off record at 9:20 AM to discuss agreement further. Recalled at 9:40 AM with same appearances. State - if defendant's stance has changed - State recommends 2 years probation with same fines and costs and other conditions of: AODA and follow thru, no alcohol and no entry into any bars, taverns or similar establishments, employment/school, 250 hours of community service, take all medications as prescribed by medical doctor or treating physician, attend at least one AA/NA or similar self-help program per week. Erickson - her client now prefers to accept probation with no jail time and conditions as previously stated by State. Erickson makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Daniels makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1 and #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years, concurrent to each other, with the following conditions: AODA and follow thru and aftercare of any current treatment and continue inpatient if needed, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 250 hours of community service, take all medications as prescribed by medical doctor or treating physician, attend at least one AA/NA or similar self-help program per week, count #1 - $100.00 fine plus costs - to be paid within the first year of probation, count #3 - costs only - to be paid in the first year of probation, submit DNA sample with expunction rights given, right to appeal, adjourned.
Jury trial on July 6, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Amanda L Daniels in court.  Attorney Linsday Erickson does not appear. Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 4:25 PM. Also called 16CM16.
